On the route, the mail can run over several other servers on the Internet.
Bennie can then call the content from his provider.
Are traditional e-mails being read on their way through the network?
Most mails are read by software robots on the go several times.
The sender’s provider usually checks whether the mail carries a malicious program as an attachment.
A virus check is also performed on the recipient systems.
In addition, the providers check whether it is a annoying and unwanted spam email that is deleted immediately or at least sorted away into a spam folder.
Do the robots have another task?
For systems such as Gmail, the robot also determines the information Google needs to place context advertising.
If Anna and Benni communicate via email about their upcoming holiday trip, Google can display corresponding links to holiday offers.
