In companies, administrators often have the opportunity to read electronic mail.
The law enforcement agencies and intelligence agencies also have legal means to intercept or take notice of e-mails.
In addition, there are possible illegal spying actions.
Is it possible to protect emails from reading?
Encryption according to the OpenPGP standard allows an e-mail to be effectively encrypted against read-through.
It is also possible to hide the metadata of an e-mail communication with great technical effort, so that it is not even possible to easily recognize who has communicated with whom.
